name: cyanogen
Reason: 1,3-dianhydride compounds have a melting point around -100°C due to the presence of two carbonyl groups, which can participate in dipole-dipole interactions and increase the melting point by approximately +20°C. The cyanogen group introduces a strong dipole moment, which can increase the melting point by approximately +50°C. The presence of two carbonyl groups and the cyanogen group can increase the melting point by approximately +70°C.
